On most LCDs (at least Sharp's one) LCD logic needs to be activated before
powering on the backlight, otherwise some display's startup artefacts 
will be seen.

Signed-off-by: Nicolas Colombain <nicolas.colombain@armadeus.com>
Signed-off-by: Julien Boibessot <julien.boibessot@armadeus.com>

Index: linux-2.6.29/drivers/video/imxfb.c
===================================================================
--- linux-2.6.29.orig/drivers/video/imxfb.c	2009-05-26 19:35:11.000000000 +0200
+++ linux-2.6.29/drivers/video/imxfb.c	2009-05-26 19:37:34.000000000 +0200
@@ -392,10 +392,10 @@
 
 	writel(RMCR_LCDC_EN, fbi->regs + LCDC_RMCR);
 
-	if (fbi->backlight_power)
-		fbi->backlight_power(1);
 	if (fbi->lcd_power)
 		fbi->lcd_power(1);
+	if (fbi->backlight_power)
+		fbi->backlight_power(1);
 }
 
